        congr with ω
        calc
          ∏ k, inner ℝ (X (I k).1 ω) (X (I k).2 ω)
          _ = ∏ k, (if (I k).1 = i then -1 else 1) * (if (I k).2 = i then -1 else 1) * inner ℝ (X (I k).1 ω) (X (I k).2 ω) := by
            congr! with k; split_ifs with hk₁ hk₂ hk₂ <;> simp [hk₁, hk₂, Y]
          _ = -∏ k, inner ℝ (X (I k).1 ω) (X (I k).2 ω) := by
            rw [prod_mul_distrib, prod_mul_distrib]
            simp [prod_ite, ← pow_add, hI'']
      rw [h8]
      simp
    exact h7
```

Now we've shown that the integral over odd families of indices is zero. Next, we decompose the sum over all families into even and odd parts.

```tactics
